overview
    https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromiumos/docs/+/HEAD/containers_and_vms.md

image server site
    https://us.images.linuxcontainers.org/

Management
	start in Crosh (Ctrl+Alt+T)
	Start and log in to termina default vm.
		vmc list
			shows VMs.  
			termina is defualt.
		vmc start termina
			starts and logs in to termina
		or:
		vsh termina
			difference from above?

	lxc list
		shows containers
	lxc start <container>
		if doesn't work, logout and run 'vmc container termina penguin'

Flatpak error 'Can't mount proc on /newroot/proc'
	from termina prompt
		`lxc config set penguin security.nesting true`
		`lxc restart penguin`



lxd
    manage application containers
    https://linuxcontainers.org/lxd/introduction/


New distro images can be created either with vmc or with lxd
    https://gist.github.com/rstacruz/aeb2273d19e5f5ffbe27a973cb82717f
    https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/Chrome_OS_devices/Crostini#Create_the_container


lxc
    image
        list    show downloaded os images
    storage
        info default    show storage info
